🧠⚖️ LCES is about procedural literacy — a skill that protects you when systems start to break down.

You don’t notice it when things are working.  
You feel it when they’re not.

🔹 It matters when:

• ❌ A claim is denied  
• 📄 A form goes missing  
• ⏳ A deadline appears out of nowhere  
• 📭 An agency stops responding  
• 🗂 HR says they “can’t locate the file”  
• 🏥 A hospital refuses to release records  
• 🎓 A school district hides behind “policy”

These are not just legal issues.  
They are life problems with procedural consequences.

And most people only recognize that when it’s too late.

🔹 LCES is not about courtrooms.

It’s about thinking clearly inside systems that were never designed for you.

🔹 The reality:

You don’t rise to the moment.  
You fall to your level of preparation.

🔥 You wouldn’t wait for a fire to learn where the exits are.

Don’t wait for a crisis to learn how systems actually work.

